foia:ProcessedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: DOI reported that it received 6,168 requests during FY12. We now know that the actual number of received requests was 6,195. This is reflected in the following corrections in the "Number Received During Fiscal Year from Last Year's Annual Report" column: BIA's received requests increased from 1,696 to 1,700; BLM's received requests increased from 979 to 983; BSEE's received requests increased from 174 to 175; FWS's received requests increased from 1,226 to 1,238; NPS's received requests increased from 921 to 925; and SOL's received requests increased from 78 to 80.

DOI reported that it processed 6,285 requests during FY12. We now know that the actual number of processed requests was 6,306. This is reflected in the following corrections in the "Number Processed During Fiscal Year from Last Year's Annual Report" column: BLM's processed requests increased from 1,003 to 1,006; BSEE's processed requests increased from 151 to 157; FWS's processed requests increased from 1,260 to 1,263; NPS's processed requests increased from 906 to 908; OIG's processed requests increased from 105 to 108; SOL's processed requests increased from 70 to 75; and USGS's processed requests decreased from 165 to 164.

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: DOI reported 449 backlogged requests at the end of FY12. We now know that the actual number of backlogged requests was 463. This is reflected in the following corrections in the "Number of Backlogged Requests as of End of the Fiscal Year from Previous Annual Report" column: BIA's backlog decreased from 34 to 30; BLM's backlog decreased from 86 to 84; BSEE's backlog increased from 20 to 40; FWS's backlog increased from 68 to 75; NPS's backlog decreased from 51 to 49; OS's backlog decreased from 54 to 50; OSM's backlog increased from 4 to 5; SOL's backlog decreased from 56 to 53; and USGS's backlog increased from 0 to 1.
